<div>
  <h2>The Solution</h2>

  <div class="side-by-side">
    <p class="big">Six Tournaments, Six Unique Looks.</p>
    <p>
      Instead of treating Code Freedom as a single ongoing event, I positioned
      each tournament as its own unique brand, ensuring fresh visuals while
      maintaining consistency.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="side-by-side">
    <p class="big">Breaking Boundaries</p>
    <p>
      Initially, the Guard could only approve plain white backgrounds, limiting
      creative impact. I developed bold, strategic design proposals that
      convinced them to expand their branding approach—leading to a more
      dynamic, engaging campaign. Convincing the US Army was no easy task, but
      it quickly became a rewarding win for everyone involved.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="side-by-side">
    <p class="big">The Cinematic Factor</p>
    <p>
      I directed six distinct event trailers, ensuring each had its own visual
      identity while maintaining a cohesive high-energy esports aesthetic. The
      Code Freedom logo reveal was treated as a cinematic moment, giving the
      brand an emblematic, franchise-worthy presence. From there, I developed
      unique trailer concepts for each of the six events, driving a high level
      of engagement for the campaign's duration.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="side-by-side">
  <div>
    <p class="big">Revealing the Code Freedom Style</p>
    <p>
      We revealed Code Freedom to the world through a cinematic reveal trailer
